      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MASTER MCGRAW (3) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 4.5 lengths at this track in a handy 29.54 beating Fearless Bandit. Fair draw can see a good run and goes well over this trip. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Expected to go well again. FLASH ETHICS (1) drifted back from the inside but sliced through to hit the frame when a 6 length third (30.07) at this track in Grade 4/5. Comes out of a hot form race last start. Will give a great sight again. BOOM BAM RANGER (8) has a strong overall record having five wins and three places from 10 starts but was out of the money last time when sixth (30.34) over 520m at Q Parklands. Form at the trip excellent including four wins. Expected to feature on best form. DENNIS KEEPING (7) was strongly fancied last time but finished fifth (22.65) at Bulli, bringing a two-run winning streak to an end. Comes out of a solid form race last start.",
